{"word":"H1713 - דָּגַל - dâgal - daw-gal' - Banners","slug":"H1713","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Original: </strong><span class=\"hebrewOrGreek\">דָּגַל</span>"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Transliteration: </strong>dâgal"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Phonetic: </strong>daw-gal'"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Short Definition: </strong>Banners"},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<b>&#x05D3;&#x05BC;&#x05D2;&#x05DC; - da&#x0302;gal</b> - <i>daw-gal'</i><p/>A primitive root; to <i>flaunt</i>, that is, <i>raise a flag</i>; figuratively to <i>be conspicuous: - </i>(set up, with) banners, chiefest."},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Cognate:</strong> <a href=\"#/H1714\">H1714</a>"}]}